WEBVTT

00:00:00.936 --> 00:00:09.650
Good evening, family. Thank you for joining us again tonight. It's Diana and Brandon, and we're excited to be here.

00:00:09.651 --> 00:00:19.105
We have some things in our heart, but I don't have a lot; I'm just going to pray with you all. I know we came on a little bit later than normal.

00:00:19.106 --> 00:00:28.745
I try to come on by then, but as you're driving around like we were today, we could feel the presence.

00:00:28.746 --> 00:00:32.777
I told Diana, 'Don't you just feel the presence of the Lord so strongly?'And she could, too.

00:00:32.778 --> 00:00:41.598
It was right after we watched Billy Burke last night; the presence of the Lord was tangible when he was in Orlando.

00:00:41.599 --> 00:00:54.636
Truly, I have never experienced through a phone or a device watching and feeling the presence of the Lord fill your car or your house like that.

00:00:54.637 --> 00:01:17.971
It lingered all night and all day. As I was seeking Him and as I went to the prayer group last night, I had an open-eyed vision of Jesus.

00:01:17.972 --> 00:01:26.400
He came, and I didn't know that Diana had been praying for me that afternoon.

00:01:26.401 --> 00:01:34.966
After I told her what happened, she started crying and said, 'Brandon, I was interceding for you, just asking God to give you a refreshing.

00:01:34.967 --> 00:01:46.096
I know you pour out so much and you're tired a lot.'She said, 'I was in my own private prayer time this morning, and I was praying for you.

00:01:46.097 --> 00:02:05.640
I asked the Lord to become real to Braden even more, help him, and give him strength.'When I went to prayer that night—which was Sunday night, I guess—my life just runs together.

00:02:05.641 --> 00:02:18.498
Last night, He spoke to me, and I said, 'Lord, I miss You.'All of a sudden, I just closed my eyes, and Jesus appeared before me in a vision, like He does whenever I'm on here.

00:02:18.499 --> 00:02:27.001
He started talking to me about some things that were very private, encouraging me just like she was asking.

00:02:27.002 --> 00:02:36.366
Because of all the things that I had delivered this last week, it was hard. I said, 'Lord, I need refreshing. Is everything okay?

00:02:36.367 --> 00:02:52.003
Are we cool right now?'And He said, 'Well, why wouldn't it be?'I said, 'Well, I've had a rough week.'And He said, 'Brandon, you just need to be refreshed. You're dry.

00:02:52.004 --> 00:03:16.399
You're thirsty.'You know, ladies and gentlemen, when you are so used to going through the valley of life, He said, 'Once you pass a certain test—Jesus said this to me yesterday—once you pass a certain test in school, you don't keep going there.

00:03:16.400 --> 00:03:31.119
You graduate.'As you are in the body of Christ, as you are on the potter's wheel and as you go from glory to glory, you don't camp in the valley.

00:03:31.120 --> 00:03:37.155
You don't camp in what you're going through for the refining fire.

00:03:37.156 --> 00:03:47.586
The refining fire is for a season, and once you pass the test, you don't have to take it again.

00:03:47.587 --> 00:04:22.997
He said, 'Brandon, you went through those things and you passed those tests, but you're so used to camping around what you had been through in the past.'From working at my grandmother's, working at the church, and having Megan, you build a wall of defense where you're always looking for the next blow.

00:04:22.998 --> 00:04:32.194
You feel that victim mentality where you walk through life feeling like you're always going through something because you're growing from glory to glory.

00:04:32.195 --> 00:04:50.688
But those tests were for that season of life. The Lord says as you grow and mature, those things become the tests that you passed.

00:04:50.689 --> 00:04:55.452
Just like in fifth, sixth, or seventh grade, you don't go back and repeat those.

00:04:55.452 --> 00:05:13.128
You just take what you learned and add to it. You keep going until you graduate.

00:05:13.129 --> 00:05:21.283
You always remember what you learned, but you never have to take the test that you took to get to the next level.

00:05:21.284 --> 00:05:32.877
You go from glory to glory. That's what He was showing me: that season is done, and He is taking me somewhere new.

00:05:32.878 --> 00:05:43.119
There are seasons of blessing and refreshing in every believer's life. It's not always about the valley.

00:05:43.120 --> 00:05:57.519
We go through hard times in our Christian walk, and that's what makes us stronger. Diana found this man who had died and went to heaven.

00:05:57.520 --> 00:06:21.722
In his testimony, he came back and said his mother told him in heaven, 'Don't forget what pain feels like, because you won't have any of it up here.'Don't take it for granted.

00:06:21.723 --> 00:06:35.514
Pain causes you to grow; trials cause you to grow. There are no trials up there to spur you to grow. The hard times are what refines you.

00:06:35.514 --> 00:06:49.338
A lot of times, when your flesh is screaming the loudest is when God has His hand on that potter's wheel and He's pushing down.

00:06:49.339 --> 00:06:56.228
Does God cause the pain? No. I want to tell you God is a rewarder of those who diligently seek Him.

00:06:56.229 --> 00:07:06.858
He is a blesser, not a curser. But because we live in a fallen world, hard times come.

00:07:06.859 --> 00:07:14.440
I always stay on God's side; God does not put sickness on people to teach them a lesson.

00:07:14.441 --> 00:07:19.256
I don't believe that. There's no sickness in heaven, so how can He give it to you?

00:07:19.257 --> 00:07:34.351
When you get to heaven, He doesn't have any sickness there, and He and the devil aren't buddies joining up to inflict His kids. What kind of father would do that?

00:07:34.352 --> 00:07:57.616
The Bible says, 'If you, being evil, give good gifts to your children, how much more does your heavenly Father give good gifts to those that love Him?'He's not giving snakes or sickness to teach you something.

00:07:57.617 --> 00:08:16.727
Because we live in a fallen world and go through life, it molds us and you grow—and also because of our own dumb decisions.

00:08:16.728 --> 00:08:45.578
But regarding the valley, the man said, 'Don't forget the way pain feels because you won't feel any in heaven.'The trial makes you grow.

00:08:45.579 --> 00:09:05.349
She said, 'And don't forget what touch feels like in this way, because it's different in heaven.'When he went to heaven—and I know he had an authentic encounter, this man wept the whole time—the glory of the Lord was present.

00:09:05.350 --> 00:09:22.173
He was a druggie and had a massive heart attack, and when he went up there, he had all this about the Father and all the inadequacies that we feel because God is so perfect.

00:09:22.174 --> 00:09:26.991
But every single thing he said was things that Jesus had said to me.

00:09:26.992 --> 00:09:34.239
Every single thing, not every single thing, but a lot of them. I don't, because that's exaggeration.

00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:45.973
Some of the things he said the Lord said to him were what the Lord said to me privately in the visitations I've had with him, and I thought, he said that to him too?

00:09:45.974 --> 00:09:53.759
Isn't that amazing that he'll help you through it? That you can't mess your life up?

00:09:53.760 --> 00:10:00.415
The footsteps of the righteous are ordered of the Lord. Brandon, he said that to me. The footsteps of the righteous are ordered of the Lord.

00:10:00.416 --> 00:10:08.595
No matter how hard you try, you couldn't mess your life up if you're seeking me and you're looking towards my face.

00:10:08.596 --> 00:10:18.398
He said, You can't mess your life up because I'll turn what the devil meant for bad and turn it around for good for you, Brandon, if you're always looking for me.

00:10:18.399 --> 00:10:27.850
No matter how bad you mess your life up, how bad you might think you've messed your life up, if you're seeking the Lord, he'll turn it on a dime.

00:10:27.851 --> 00:10:37.679
It's about putting Jesus first. We must learn to put Jesus first. He is everything.

00:10:37.680 --> 00:10:52.078
If you put him first in your marriage, if you put him first with your children, if you put him first in your finances—that's why the Bible says, you know, a lot of people get all upset when you tell them about tithing and giving, but we were forced to learn how to tithe.

00:10:52.079 --> 00:10:58.319
Our church forced us to tithe. Because we were on staff, if we didn't tithe, they'd fire you.

00:10:58.320 --> 00:11:08.958
And so I knew whenever you're forced to learn how to tithe, it then becomes habit because we worked there for so many years.

00:11:08.959 --> 00:11:14.319
So people say, Oh, I don't believe in tithing. Oh, I believe with all my heart.

00:11:14.320 --> 00:11:23.939
I believe in tithing more than—I'm telling you, I have got the revelation of tithing, not because of something that I wanted, but because I was forced to.

00:11:23.940 --> 00:11:31.565
And I thank God for Mark all the time. Pastor Mark, he taught us the fundamentals of tithing.

00:11:31.566 --> 00:11:40.712
It was, like I said, strong-armed, but I'm thankful that he did it because if he wouldn't have done it, I wouldn't have got the revelation of it.

00:11:40.713 --> 00:11:52.799
I was a tipper. I was a tipper. I'd give God a little bit here and there, and you give him what you could or whatever, whenever it was convenient.

00:11:52.800 --> 00:12:05.861
But as we grew and God started speaking to Diana, she got her education, her master's degree, and did all that through her schooling and pushing as hard as we did.

00:12:05.862 --> 00:12:10.233
But then the Lord gave us an idea outside of what we naturally would have thought.

00:12:10.234 --> 00:12:17.617
It was Diana that had the revelation. It's amazing how many times the Lord has used her to help our family.

00:12:17.618 --> 00:12:24.557
Husbands, listen to your wives. They have wisdom, and wives, listen to your husbands.

00:12:24.558 --> 00:12:31.198
But I'm just saying don't always just think that you have it all and that you know God, well, I'm the head of the house and you better listen to me.

00:12:31.199 --> 00:12:43.838
I thank God that she had the idea for eBay and Poshmark. Thank God it came from a Holy Ghost-inspired idea of desperation. Couldn't pay our electric bill.

00:12:43.839 --> 00:12:56.131
But I'm saying as we tithed and we gave, we kept tithing and we keep giving, and it's become foundation in our life where God is always first. That was where I was going with that.

00:12:56.132 --> 00:13:07.855
By keeping God first in your marriage, praying together, reading the Bible together, reading little books like this together, we keep our marriage fresh that way.

00:13:07.856 --> 00:13:12.313
And I don't always say there haven't been hard days; we go through it.

00:13:12.314 --> 00:13:24.626
But we know if we pray together, we stay together, and we take communion together, and we know that if we seek him together, we'll find him.

00:13:24.627 --> 00:13:32.165
I've learned to lean on her discernment a lot. I believe there's a lot of discernment in women.

00:13:32.166 --> 00:13:36.264
God has gifted women with great discernment. Don't you agree?

00:13:36.265 --> 00:13:40.476
They're like, it's like Billy Burke says, they're the rear guard of the household.

00:13:40.477 --> 00:13:43.557
They're able to see things a lot of times that the man doesn't see.

00:13:43.558 --> 00:13:52.320
And when she gets these emails and people are always saying they've got something going on and Diana says, I have to check.

00:13:52.321 --> 00:13:55.892
I have to pray about that. Let's pray about that together more.

00:13:55.893 --> 00:14:01.056
And I say, You see something I don't see. Okay. Well, I trust it.

00:14:01.057 --> 00:14:06.501
And she says, I don't always trust the motive behind the individual. You have to pray.

00:14:06.502 --> 00:14:14.175
And we learn as you intercede and as you pray and you grow, God will develop you and you'll go from glory to glory.

00:14:14.176 --> 00:14:29.886
But I was praying over things today and the anointing and the presence of the Lord was so strong, and he was talking to me about what's about to happen.

00:14:29.887 --> 00:14:36.936
Going and praying into 2026, this is a year you can't just let your guard down.

00:14:36.937 --> 00:14:43.999
You must be spiritually alert. 2026 is going to be a high alert year.

00:14:44.000 --> 00:14:48.799
We must pray for our country concerning terrorist attacks, Red Dawn experiences.

00:14:48.800 --> 00:14:56.564
Oh, Brandon, you said—I'm telling you by the spirit of God, you must have your eyes open.

00:14:56.565 --> 00:15:14.320
Do not become dazed for the days that are ahead concerning this nation, concerning our president, his safety, and all the things that I keep telling you and talking to you all about.

00:15:14.321 --> 00:15:20.161
This is a time to have your senses heightened all around the world. You say, Well, I'm not in America.

00:15:20.162 --> 00:15:32.110
Well, if you live in Australia, if you live in Europe, if you have your spiritual discernment heightened by praying and fasting, by seeking him, you will find him.

00:15:32.111 --> 00:15:38.052
This is a time not for the church to be asleep. You must wake up.

00:15:38.053 --> 00:15:50.719
I'm telling you, closing out 2025 and really coming alive in 2026 even more. You need to have your eyes open.

00:15:50.720 --> 00:16:12.382
I have a great warning going into the future and praying over this year, praying over 2026, but I was seeing the old generals and he said, Go back to the wells, the wells of the revival.

00:16:12.383 --> 00:16:30.576
You see the picture behind us? That Thanksgiving picture was what I saw in the spirit when the Pilgrims came and they put their hands together and they made a covenant to God at Plymouth Rock.

00:16:30.577 --> 00:16:47.615
And I saw an actual rock that they stood around and they prayed and they took communion and they dedicated the land of America as one nation that they would have a God-fearing—they dedicated this land, this property where we are.

00:16:47.616 --> 00:17:05.519
We dedicate this land to Jesus that we will be a people that live by faith, that have a freedom of religion and all the things that they sought out for.

00:17:05.520 --> 00:17:13.688
The Lord said to me, he said, Brandon—he brought it up to me tonight, Brandon—those prayers still go before me.

00:17:13.689 --> 00:17:22.632
The prayers of your founding fathers clear back at Plymouth Rock. They go before me.

00:17:22.633 --> 00:17:35.729
George Washington's prayers on the battlefield when he was fighting the British, when he was fighting the battle and he was weary, and I gave him supernatural strength to fight for the land.

00:17:35.730 --> 00:17:41.733
When George Washington had bullets flying all around him, they said bullets were all in his cloak.

00:17:41.734 --> 00:17:49.438
His jacket, what he had on, all those bullets from—he had bullets all through his clothes because they were that close to hitting him.

00:17:49.439 --> 00:17:53.752
But the hand of the Lord was on him to protect him for this nation.

00:17:53.753 --> 00:18:12.079
And as he was praying, God, give me strength to finish this battle, God supernaturally gave him a strength, knowing that there was going to be a Diana and a Brandon standing here today praying for you in America saying Jesus is coming.

00:18:12.080 --> 00:18:21.965
Jesus is coming. Do you know our friend? We had over 100 people get saved this last video. That's what it's all about to us.

00:18:21.966 --> 00:18:31.772
97, Braden said so far just on the livestream, and then how many people on emails and everything else, has been over the top from the other videos.

00:18:31.773 --> 00:18:44.582
But as I saw in the spirit George Washington fighting the battle and God gave him strength and he prayed that this nation would be a nation that feared God.

00:18:44.583 --> 00:18:54.629
Those prayers still go before the Father. He's not forgotten it. And he said to me, "You will not be a goat nation.

00:18:54.630 --> 00:18:59.587
You will be a sheep nation."And a great shaking to awaken is coming to this land.

00:18:59.588 --> 00:19:10.239
It will not be a land that turns its back and does things against me, becoming a goat nation from the Father.

00:19:10.240 --> 00:19:18.475
We will remain a sheep nation. I want to be a sheep; I don't want to be a goat.

00:19:18.476 --> 00:19:26.472
So I want to encourage you all today: America is not done for. America is not falling off.

00:19:26.473 --> 00:19:36.605
Well, we see Mamdani, or whatever his name is, up there in New York and all these things—yeah, there are some radical things happening right now.

00:19:36.606 --> 00:19:55.279
Braden had a list of all the churches in the last 24 months in Texas alone; 48 mosques were raised up in Texas in this area right here in the last 24 months.

00:19:55.280 --> 00:20:15.840
48 mosques were created or raised up in Texas. Ladies and gentlemen, does anybody know this stuff is going on?

00:20:15.841 --> 00:20:29.119
As we see this stuff happen, a great shaking is coming. Go back to what he said: go back to the family units.

00:20:29.120 --> 00:20:36.959
Go back to the foundation. Go back to the basics, the ABCs. Don't get out of the ABCs.

00:20:36.960 --> 00:20:52.903
There are so many people that have forgotten the ABCs. What does that mean? The fundamentals of Christianity.

00:20:52.904 --> 00:20:58.719
It all ties together, what he's telling me and what I'm trying to tell y'all tonight.

00:20:58.720 --> 00:21:06.326
Don't forget kindergarten; don't forget it because you're going to use what you learned in first grade.

00:21:06.327 --> 00:21:14.158
It all goes from glory to glory. It's the same way with your faith and your walk with the Father.

00:21:14.159 --> 00:21:20.992
You learn your confession. You learn how to speak things and call those things that be not as though they were in Romans.

00:21:20.993 --> 00:21:25.257
You've got to learn that life and death is in the power of your tongue.

00:21:25.258 --> 00:21:30.794
The more you speak out of your mouth, what you're saying is what you're living.

00:21:30.795 --> 00:21:37.942
What you said yesterday is what you'll live tomorrow. What you're living today is what you said yesterday.

00:21:37.943 --> 00:21:48.754
You must understand that life and death is in the power of your tongue. Most people just say things flippantly.

00:21:48.755 --> 00:21:53.796
Even Pastor Chip and Candace say all the time, "What's the first thing that comes out of your mouth?

00:21:53.797 --> 00:22:06.639
What's your first response?"What's your first response to the circumstance when the doctor gives you a bad report? "Well, your blood pressure is too high.

00:22:06.640 --> 00:22:15.962
We're going to have to put you on blood thinners."They're going to do all this stuff because you get these bad reports, but what's the first thing?

00:22:15.963 --> 00:22:26.771
"Well, I guess I'm dying. My marriage is going to heck. My kids are going to hell.

00:22:26.772 --> 00:22:33.172
My finances aren't doing any good."You speak all those things out of your mouth, and the more you speak them, you'll have them.

00:22:33.173 --> 00:22:42.071
Most people go, "I don't believe that,"but the devil knows the power of your tongue and its influence.

00:22:42.072 --> 00:22:52.222
Even when it comes to God, we are made in His image. As He is, so are we in this world.

00:22:52.223 --> 00:23:03.276
He spoke it, and it was. Remember what I told you: God's words do not return to Him void.

00:23:03.277 --> 00:23:17.149
They will accomplish that for which He sent them. When I went to the throne room and the Lord was speaking, none of His words died.

00:23:17.150 --> 00:23:29.599
They all became seeds before the throne. As they went together and all the letters came together, they formed sentences right before my face.

00:23:29.600 --> 00:23:49.142
They became a mustard seed in front of my face. All His words came out of Him and formed a mustard seed that started to grow because they didn't die.

00:23:49.143 --> 00:24:03.053
Everything the Lord says never returns to Him void. He does not speak to hear Himself talk; He speaks to make real things happen in a real world.

00:24:03.054 --> 00:24:13.870
That's what Oral Roberts even said: "Make no little plans here. Believe God for big."You've got to speak to your mountain.

00:24:13.871 --> 00:24:19.171
Your mountain needs to hear your voice because we're made in His image.

00:24:19.172 --> 00:24:26.565
So I'm trying to tell us as Christians to always speak life into the circumstances.

00:24:26.566 --> 00:24:34.051
If you get mad and say something stupid, repent and say, "I thank you, Lord, that there's a crop failure over those words.

00:24:34.052 --> 00:24:53.985
I don't want my words to bring that."There was a family, the Shooks, when I was a teenager; they had a church in Fort Worth and they would always say, "Is that what you want?

00:24:53.986 --> 00:25:03.590
You'll have what you say."They'd always be quick to correct you. I've always thought about that.

00:25:03.591 --> 00:25:08.326
You'll have what you say; life and death is in the power of your tongue.

00:25:08.327 --> 00:25:14.719
So I want you to really think about things when we talk about America.

00:25:14.720 --> 00:25:38.479
We want to speak life, peace, and joy. But these things I'm telling you are warnings. We need to pray and take our authority. I have to warn you.

00:25:38.480 --> 00:25:53.423
I told you 1 Corinthians 5:5; the Lord said an acceleration of 1 Corinthians 5:5 will be on the ones that are not awake because they're still asleep.

00:25:53.424 --> 00:26:02.457
A lot of the pastors behind the pulpits are preaching a lukewarm gospel.

00:26:02.458 --> 00:26:15.960
The Lord said they must start to tell my people what I told you about Oral Roberts and the great awakening, the last call.

00:26:15.961 --> 00:26:17.553
He had this visitation, and it was so strong that it shook him.

00:26:17.554 --> 00:26:38.437
He said, "This is me telling the people that the soon return of my son is at hand.

00:26:38.438 --> 00:26:50.389
They must start preaching fire behind the pulpits."The Lord told me 1 Corinthians 5:5 was going to start to be amplified.

00:26:50.390 --> 00:27:05.038
He said, "I've warned them through 2025 to get prepared and to start telling my people that I'm coming, and they have disobeyed me.

00:27:05.039 --> 00:27:10.479
For much is given, much is required."Brandon, much is given, much is required.

00:27:10.480 --> 00:27:42.034
I've given them celebrity and no lack of finances—some make millions of dollars every month—yet they've not listened to what I've told them to do by telling the people about Revelation, repentance, and seeking me.

00:27:42.035 --> 00:27:56.398
John the Baptist yelled. How many times did we hear the prophetic voices in the Old Testament warn that the Messiah was coming the first time?

00:27:56.399 --> 00:28:14.234
Isaiah yelled and yelled. People said, "Oh, hundreds of years passed by."The Bible says there will be scoffers.

00:28:14.235 --> 00:28:26.276
Peter said, "There'll be scoffers.""Well, when is the coming of the Lord? We've heard this before."But people will scoff.

00:28:26.277 --> 00:28:34.682
But I'm telling you, just as in the days of Noah, so will it be when the Son of Man returns.

00:28:34.683 --> 00:28:39.278
They mocked Noah over and over. 'Oh, it's going to rain. Oh, Noah.

00:28:39.279 --> 00:28:55.897
Oh, crazy Noah.'When I had that vision and saw the timeline, I told everybody, 'The Lord allowed me to see Noah.'I got to see Noah, and he had a big nose.

00:28:55.898 --> 00:29:05.204
He had a ginormous nose and his ears were ginormous. I thought, 'What in the world is that?

00:29:05.205 --> 00:29:10.398
Who is this?'As I was looking, the Lord said, 'That's Noah.'I could see him building the ark.

00:29:10.399 --> 00:29:15.080
I could see everything. The trees were massive and green; it was beautiful.

00:29:15.081 --> 00:29:20.415
The canopy above the earth was pink with beautiful colors, and it was actually humming.

00:29:20.416 --> 00:29:28.358
It had noise. I don't know why, but the atmosphere above the world...

00:29:28.359 --> 00:29:37.869
all the trees were huge. There was no death. The earth was gorgeous. It looked so pretty the way the plants were.

00:29:37.870 --> 00:29:50.674
Compared to what we have now—I don't want to say there was no death, there was death there—but the greenery wasn't like it is now.

00:29:50.675 --> 00:29:58.719
Our trees are nothing compared to what I saw when I was there in the spirit.

00:29:58.720 --> 00:30:05.178
It's the same thing when I told you Adam was talking to a dinosaur-looking thing.

00:30:05.179 --> 00:30:16.041
I saw Adam and he was ripped; he had muscles. He was talking to what looked like a long-neck dinosaur.

00:30:16.042 --> 00:30:24.169
I thought this was amazing, but the Lord showed me the timeframe.

00:30:24.170 --> 00:30:29.728
He went through each thousand years and played it before my eyes like a movie screen.

00:30:29.729 --> 00:30:36.531
I could see it all playing before me. Everything was so beautiful; I described it the best I could.

00:30:36.532 --> 00:30:48.912
I could see them building the Colosseum, the pyramids, and even the Great Wall of China.

00:30:48.913 --> 00:30:53.431
It all played before me: battles, kingdoms, empires rising and falling.

